text: Eduardo Segundo Brizuela del Moral (20 August 1944 - 25 August 2021) was an Argentine Radical Civic Union (UCR) politician. He was governor of Catamarca Province from 2003 to 2011. He was also a Senator from 2001 until 2003 and a member of the Chamber of Deputies from 2011 until his death. Brizuela del Moral was born in San Fernando del Valle de Catamarca, Argentina. Brizuela del Moral died on 25 August 2021 in San Fernando del Valle de Catamarca from pneumonia caused by a stroke, five days after his 77th birthday. ==References== Category:1944 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Catamarca Province Category:Argentine politicians
